  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Stokeworth\" title=\"House Stokeworth\"><img alt=\"House Stokeworth.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/37/House_Stokeworth.svg/50px-House_Stokeworth.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/37/House_Stokeworth.svg/75px-House_Stokeworth.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/37/House_Stokeworth.svg/100px-House_Stokeworth.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Lord</span><br />Alyn Stokeworth</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Stokeworth\" title=\"House Stokeworth\"><img alt=\"House Stokeworth.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/37/House_Stokeworth.svg/50px-House_Stokeworth.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/37/House_Stokeworth.svg/75px-House_Stokeworth.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/37/House_Stokeworth.svg/100px-House_Stokeworth.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Brune_avenges_Stokeworth_by_Ertac_Altinoz_(The_Rise_of_the_Dragon).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Brune avenges Stokeworth by Ertac Altinoz (The Rise of the Dragon).jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f6/Brune_avenges_Stokeworth_by_Ertac_Altinoz_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/350px-Brune_avenges_Stokeworth_by_Ertac_Altinoz_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"313\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f6/Brune_avenges_Stokeworth_by_Ertac_Altinoz_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/525px-Brune_avenges_Stokeworth_by_Ertac_Altinoz_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/f6/Brune_avenges_Stokeworth_by_Ertac_Altinoz_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/700px-Brune_avenges_Stokeworth_by_Ertac_Altinoz_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg 2x\" /></a><div><a href=\"/index.php/Bernarr_Brune\" title=\"Bernarr Brune\">Bernarr Brune</a> avenges Alyn Stokeworth's (bottom) death by Ertaç Altınöz for <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Titles</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Stokeworth\" title=\"Lord of Stokeworth\">Lord of Stokeworth</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Stokeworth\" title=\"House Stokeworth\">House Stokeworth</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Crownlands\" title=\"Crownlands\">Crownlands</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/37_AC\" title=\"37 AC\">37&#160;AC</a><br />west of the <a href=\"/index.php/Gods_Eye\" title=\"Gods Eye\">Gods Eye</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Samantha_Stokeworth\" title=\"Samantha Stokeworth\">Samantha Stokeworth</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Sons_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Sons of the Dragon\">The Sons of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Alyn Stokeworth</b> was the Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/Stokeworth\" title=\"Stokeworth\">Stokeworth</a> and the head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stokeworth\" title=\"House Stokeworth\">House Stokeworth</a> during the reign of kings <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Aenys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aenys I Targaryen\">Aenys I Targaryen</a>. He served as <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a> for both of them.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Alyn_Stokeworth&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Lord Alyn was named <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a> by King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a> after the death of Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Osmund_Strong\" title=\"Osmund Strong\">Osmund Strong</a>, the previous Hand, in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_34_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">34&#160;AC</a>. When Aegon ordered the <a href=\"/index.php/Aegonfort\" title=\"Aegonfort\">Aegonfort</a> torn down and a stone castle to be built in its place in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_35_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">35&#160;AC</a>, he assigned the task to Alyn and Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Visenya_Targaryen\" title=\"Visenya Targaryen\">Visenya Targaryen</a>, while he moved to <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a> with the rest of his court.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord Alyn brought his daughter <a href=\"/index.php/Samantha_Stokeworth\" title=\"Samantha Stokeworth\">Samantha</a> to court, who became a close friend and companion of Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aenys_I)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Aenys I)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Aegon the Conqueror died at Dragonstone in <a href=\"/index.php/37_AC\" title=\"37 AC\">37&#160;AC</a> and Alyn remained as Hand for his son and heir, King <a href=\"/index.php/Aenys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aenys I Targaryen\">Aenys I Targaryen</a>. Upon Aenys' coronation, rebellions rose throughout the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>. The first of these challenges was by a bandit <a href=\"/index.php/Outlaw\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Outlaw\">outlaw</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a> known as <a href=\"/index.php/Harren_the_Red\" title=\"Harren the Red\">Harren the Red</a>, who claimed to be a grandson of King <a href=\"/index.php/Harren_Hoare\" title=\"Harren Hoare\">Harren the Black</a>. First, Aenys commanded Lord Stokeworth to take a fleet and army to the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn\" title=\"Vale of Arryn\">Vale of Arryn</a> to put down a rebellion instigated by <a href=\"/index.php/Jonos_Arryn\" title=\"Jonos Arryn\">Jonos Arryn</a> and restore his brother <a href=\"/index.php/Ronnel_Arryn_(king)\" title=\"Ronnel Arryn (king)\">Ronnel</a> to his lordship.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>As Alyn was about to set sail to the Vale, Aenys countermanded the order, fearing that Stokeworth's departure would leave <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> undefended. Instead, Alyn was sent to the riverlands with a few hundred men to hunt down Harren the Red. Alyn personally led the campaign against Red Harren and successfully caught and cornered the outlaw king in a village west of the <a href=\"/index.php/Gods_Eye\" title=\"Gods Eye\">Gods Eye</a>. In the final fight, Harren killed Alyn but was subsequently slain by Alyn's squire, <a href=\"/index.php/Bernarr_Brune\" title=\"Bernarr Brune\">Bernarr Brune</a>. A grateful King Aenys conferred <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knighthood</a> on Brune.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aenys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aenys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Alyn_Stokeworth&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\">1.5</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\">1.6</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Sons of the Dragon.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aenys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aenys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a>